text: Rantsila is a former municipality in Northern Ostrobothnia, Finland. Since 2009, it became a part of the new municipality of Siikalatva. As of 31 December 2008, 2,001 people lived there. Neighbouring municipalities were Kestilä, Liminka, Pulkkila, Ruukki and Vihanti. It was founded in 1867. == Other websites == * Municipality of Rantsila – Official website Category:1867 establishments in Finland Category:Former municipalities of Finland
